@node "introduction" "Amitel_English.guide/introduction"
   AmiTEL is now @{" SHAREWARE " link "shareware" 0}. It's an emulation software for the norm Videotex
CEPT2 used on the French network Teletel and by a lot of BBS RTC and for the
norm Videotex CEPT3 used on the English network Prestel.

   The main purpose of this emulator is emulating the main functions of Minitel
in a window using the graphics.library to provide a better graphic interface
(keeping original WorkBench colors) and the speed of the emulation (3.5 times
faster than previous versions).

   AmiTEL is fully written in asm with AsmONE 1.29 and the user interface was
made with GadToolsBox 2.0c. The sets of fonts were integrated in the executable
file with FontAsm v1.02

   The emulator should perfectly work on all configurations with Kickstart 2.04
or more. The software was written and tested on an Amiga 1200/030 (3.1) and
tested on an Amiga 500/500+ (2.04) and Amiga 2000/030 (2.1).
@endnode

