@node "installation" "Amitel_English.guide/installation"
   To work normally, AmiTEL needs some extras files installed like this :

        'reqtools.library'         in LIBS:

        'AmiTEL.guide'             in the same drawer as AmiTEL.
        (it's the 'AmiTEL_English.guide' file renammed).

        'AmiTEL.catalog'           in LOCALE:Catalogs/English/

        'AmiTEL.key'               in L:
        (only for registered users).

   If you want to use XPRZModem, XPRBBTPro or XPRMoonDial and ARexx scripts :

        'libs/xprzmodem.library'   in LIBS:
        'Libs/xprbbtpro.library'   in LIBS:
        'Libs/xprmoondial.library' in LIBS:
        'Rexx/*.amtl'              in REXX:

   If you've already installed an old version of AmiTEL, you must delete these
   files :

        'BBTPro'                   in the same drawer as AmiTEL.

        'Minitel/*'                in FONTS:
        'Minitel.font'
        'Minitel16/*'
        'Minitel16.font'
        'Minitel80/*'
        'Minitel80.font'

        'AmiTEL.cfg'               in S:

   And you must update your phonebook file 'AmiTEL.phone' with 'update' command
(version < 2.0 only) and ARexx old files with new *.amtl files.

   An easier way of doing it, you can just click on the icon 'AmiTEL.install'
or hit the command 'Installer AmiTEL.install' for a correct installation of
AmiTEL.

   Note : Installer and AmigaGuide® are no longer distributed in the package.
@endnode

@node "Internet" "Internet"
        A certain number of Videotext servers can be accessed via the Internet,
among which the famous AMIGATEL.

        How is this possible? Simply by getting connected to the 516 port of
certain @{" sites " link "net_list" 0} , using Telnet protocol.

                        @{" Setup        " link "net_install" 0}
                        @{" Use          " link "net_start" 0}
                        @{" Servers      " link "net_list" 0}

        For additional information: http://www.mctel.fr
@endnode

@node "net_install" "net_install"
        AmiTEL uses the excellent Telser software for its connections with
Telnet. You may find Telser on every good Aminet sites or CDROM.

        To setup Telser, you may use the installer script provided with the
archive. This does a complete setup.

        You may however implement a partial setup as follows:

        o copy the file 'bin/telser' to Amitel directory
        o copy the file 'dev/telser.device_amitcp' to 'DEVS:telser.device'
        o copy the file 'libs/rawwin.library' to 'LIBS:'
        o add the command line 'assign AmiTCP: RAM:' to your 'S:User-Statup'
          file.
@endnode

@node "net_start" "net_start"
        Once Telser software has been @{" setup " link "net_install" 0} properly, you'll have to get
connected to your favorite Internet provider, and run Amitel with the following
options:

        'AmiTEL NODETACH DEVICE=telser.device UNIT=0'

        You may now add new 'numbers' to the Amitel phone book. For example,
the new AMIGATEL number would be: www.mctel.fr,516

        Then, clic on 'Dial' and when 'service:' comes up, type in 'AMIGATEL',
for example, and press the enter key on the numeric key pad (return).

        If you have problems, check, with the command 'ping www.mctel.fr', if
mctel is accessible.

        There is still an easier way to get connected to a Videotext server
with AmiTEL via the Internet. Have a look at the 'Amigatel_w3' Arexx script
which can be found in the AmiTEL archive. You'll just have to type
'rx Amigatel_w3" in a shell window or double-click the icon on the Workbench
to get connected automatically. If anyone finds something easier... :-)
@endnode

@node "net_list" "net_list"
        Here are some available Videotext servers:

        o www.mctel.fr,516

          3SUISSES, AE, AK, AMIGATEL, GAY, GUN, LIBRE, MENSA, MSG, SOSOVNI.

        o vtx.telestore.fr,516

          BISTRO, CHEZ, D2, DRESS, ETRE2, GUY, JAM, U2, VIEA2, XYZ.

        o www.agl.fr,516

          CUM.
@endnode

@node "Faq" "FAQ"
Following are the most frequently asked questions about AmiTEL:

o How to get connected on AMIGATEL via the Internet?

     Very simple: all is explained @{" here " link "internet" 0} !


o I can't get connected with my modem.

     Check whether you're using the proper init string:

        o USRobotic : ATS34=8S27=16S9=100^M
        o Hayes Opt : ATB2^M
        o Supra Fax : AT+MS=V23C,0,1200,33600^M

     If you have another modem, please feel free to send me a @{" message " link "updates" 0}


o Can I send texts that are prepared ahead of time?

     Yes, it is possible. You need to prepare your text with your favorite
     text editor, format it to a width of 39 characters. Then, when you're
     connected to the server, lunch the 'SendText.amtl' Arexx script. This
     way, your file will be properly sent to the minitel server.


o When I press Cnx/Fin, my modem does not get connected. Why?

     It's normal. Actually, the first difference between a modem and a
     minitel is that a modem gets connected automatically without for you
     to do anything manually (I think it's the V25bis protocol that takes
     care of it :-). Therefore, you need not to touch anything and wait
     till the modem gets connected by it-self.


o Ok, then why does not my modem get disconnected when I press Cnx/Fin?

     This happens with some modems which do not respond to DTR OFF signals.
     For this reason I added the 'Break' button which sends the modem the
     disconnect string it understands.


o Why can't I move the status window?

     Because it had not been supposed to from the beginning. To avoid this
     problem, use the option/tooltype NOSTATUS or uncheck the 'Status'
     option in the configuration window. This outputs the status to the
     main window rather than to a specific one.


o How do we do to get connected to 'kiosque micro'?

     Very simple: just create a new entry to the phone book with
     0836011313, 0836011414 or 0636011515 as the number. Then set the
     connection speed to at least 9600. However, be aware that only
     0836011313 benefits from time rates.


o What is the Debug function for?

     As its name tells, this function helps me to debug AmiTEL by printing
     an hexadecimal form of all that which gets in the software. This may
     also be useful for them that have an interest in designing Videotext
     pages.


o How to use a multi-serial autoconfig board?

     The only thing needed is to directly type the corresponding device name
     which is in ROM, in the appropriate gadget of the setup window. If you
     don't know the exact name, try to use a system utility such as ARTM or
     Xoper.


o  Where can I find the latest AmiTEL version?

     The latest version being developed is available at the following
     address: http://www.amitel.home.ml.org.

     Otherwise, the final versions are available on Aminet CDROMs or FTP
     sites.
@endnode

@node "starting" "Amitel_English.guide/starting"
   AmiTEL don't detaches from CLI/Shell (the 'Run' command is needed).

   The software can also be launched from the WorkBench, by simply clicking on
its icon.

   The arguments accepted by AmiTEL are :

   * @{b}NOSCREEN@{ub} opens the emulator on the Workbench screen (an 8-colored
     Workbench screen minimum is needed for the best exploitation of
     Videotex emulation).

   * @{b}MINITEL@{ub} forces the use of a Minitel in the case where the automatic
     recognition doesn't work fine or your Minitel cable always blocks
     the DCD signal (Modem by default).

   * @{b}NOLOGFILE@{ub} to not save the connections journal (AmiTEL.log).

   * @{b}NOSTATUS@{ub} to display status informations in title emulator window.

   * @{b}NOENTER@{ub} to not assign ENTER key with the ENVOI Minitel key value
     (RETURN by default).

   * @{b}DEPTH@{ub} to open AmiTEL's public screen in more than 16 colors
     (4 by default).

   * @{b}INTERLACE@{ub} to open AmiTEL's public screen in interlace mode
     (none interlace by default).

   * @{b}TOPAZ@{ub} to use Topaz 8 font
     (Workbench screen font by default).

   * @{b}PRESTEL@{ub} to use Prestel emulator mode
     (Minitel emulator mode by default).

   * @{b}QUIET@{ub} to run AmiTEL without to open serial.device.

   * @{b}SPEED=1200 to 115200@{ub} changes the transfert speed
     (1200 by default).

   * @{b}PARITY=EVEN/ODD/NONE@{ub} changes the parity
     (EVEN by default).

   * @{b}BITS=7/8@{ub} changes the number of bits
     (7 by default).

   * @{b}HANDSHAKE=RTS/XON/NONE@{ub} changes the protocol of serial device
     (NONE by default).

   * @{b}STRIPHIGHBIT@{ub} strip the high bit for the X25.

   * @{b}DEVICE=xxxxxx.device@{ub} changes the name of the serial interface
     (serial.device by default).

   * @{b}UNIT=n@{ub} changes the unit number of the serial interface
     (0 by default).

   * @{b}INIT=ATx@{ub} changes the init sequence of the modem
     (ATZ by default).

   * @{b}ESC=xxx@{ub} changes the escape sequence of the modem
     (+++ by defaut).

   * @{b}HANG=ATx@{ub} changes the hangup sequence of the modem
     (ATH by default).

   * @{b}NUM=ATDx@{ub} changes the numbering sequence of the modem
     (ATDT by default).

   * @{b}XPR=XPRxxxxxx.library@{ub} changes the name of the XPR library
     (XPRZModem.library by default).

   * @{b}BUFFER=nnnn@{ub} changes the saving buffer size
     (8192 by default).

   * @{b}M1B@{ub} to dial with an M1b Minitel.

   * @{b}GREEK@{ub} to use Greek Videotext font.

   * @{b}DETACH@{ub} to self detach from CLI.

   * @{b}ENVOI@{ub} to add ENVOI on mouse selection.

   * @{b}HELP@{ub} or @{b}?@{ub} displays all the valid parameters (under CLI).

   The arguments must be separated by a 'Space' for their correct
interpretation, in the case of CLI/Shell. These arguments are also available as
TOOLTYPEs for the icon.
@endnode

